Equations (1), (2) and (5) can be transformed into a system of coupled differential equations with initial conditions. In order to do this, Eq. (5) must be discretized with appropriate boundary conditions (see Kushnir et al. [49] for details). The solution for the time evolution of temperature in the cavity is obtain by numerically integrating the system of differential equations thus formed. We used a non-stiff solver for the injection phase and a stiff solver for the discharge and storage period. With the help of thermodynamic properties relationships, the enthalpies (h\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
